 the problem I am not sure)<br><br>The configurations:<br><br>#1 1200Tbird w a Gforce2000/400<br>256megs of (non) ddr ram<br>(that is important with an MSI MB)<br><br>#2 1000Tbird w a ELSA Erazor X2 32mb(in theory the best card we own)<br>512megs of (non) ddr ram<br><br>#3 1000Tbird w a Gforce2000/400<br>512megs of (non) ddr ram<br><br><br>Board #1 inexblicably will start re-writing its virtual ram in the middle of <br>battle. Freezing you out of doing anything at all until its done.<br>That usually results in DEAD player.<br><br>Boards #2 almost with religious regularity will need a total reboot every 45<br>min. Even if you are standing still doing nothing. This manifests as<br>choppy frames distorted polygons etc. Each frame lagging behind the other.<br>This is MOST noticible of course in Camelot. Overclocking the Video card doesnt seem to help at all (or hinder)<br><br>Board #3 The performance of this board makes me wonder if the Gforce actually<br>uses that 64megs of ram. The board manifests incredible slowdown<br>during combat sequence. You can compensate somewhat (if passively)<br>by listening to the sound because the sound apparently suffers no such<br>disfuntion. <br><br>Is there any plan to remove (what seem to me) these obvious memory leaks?<br>If there is any kind of patch or web-site with usefull info please tell me.<br>(everytime the wife dies somehow its my fault)<br>This bug in particular is making it hard to be enthused about the game.<br><br>I will admit there are good things about the game but that must wait another time.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uperceival.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Perceival</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 50<br> <font color=#E9D756>(10/30/01 11:27:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?t